/**
 * JavaMappingBridge.groovy — Compatibility layer for porting PI/PO Java mappings to CPI.
 *
 * PI/PO Java mappings use the com.sap.aii.mapping.api.* API surface:
 *   - AbstractTransformation (base class)
 *   - TransformationInput / TransformationOutput (stream I/O)
 *   - InputPayload / OutputPayload (named payload access)
 *   - MappingTrace (logging)
 *   - Container / GlobalContainer (parameter passing)
 *   - RuntimeConstants (environment info)
 *
 * CPI doesn't have these classes. This script provides a bridge layer
 * that emulates the PI/PO API surface using CPI's Message API, allowing
 * ported Java mapping logic to run with minimal changes.
 *
 * === Migration workflow ===
 *
 * 1. Take the PI/PO Java mapping source (.java file)
 * 2. Remove: import com.sap.aii.mapping.api.*
 * 3. Replace: extends AbstractTransformation → (standalone class)
 * 4. Change method signature:
 *      void transform(TransformationInput input, TransformationOutput output)
 *    →
 *      String transform(String inputPayload, Map<String, String> params)
 *    The method should return the output XML as a String.
 * 5. Replace API calls using this cheat sheet:
 *      input.getInputPayload().getInputStream()  → inputPayload (already a String)
 *      output.getOutputPayload().getOutputStream() → return String
 *      input.getInputHeader().getFieldValue("...")  → params.get("...")
 *      getTrace().addInfo("...")  → (remove or use log.info)
 *      container.getParameter("...") → params.get("...")
 * 6. Compile to .jar (Java 8 target) or paste into Groovy directly
 * 7. This bridge script calls the ported logic and handles CPI I/O
 *
 * === Usage in iFlow ===
 *
 * Set these properties on the Script step or via Content Modifier:
 *   - JavaMappingClass  : fully qualified class name (if using JAR import)
 *   - JavaMappingMethod : method name (default "transform")
 *
 * Or for inline Groovy ports, override the portedMappingLogic() method below.
 *
 * Generated by Sashay Control Tower for iFlow: {{ iflow_id }}
 */


